<section xml:id="C28.S22">
<title>Connection Formulas</title>        
  
<subsection xml:id="C28.S22.SS1">
<title>Integer <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS1.m1">\nu</Math></title>        
 
<para xml:id="C28.S22.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C28.S22.SS1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="28.22.1" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E1">{\mathrm{Mc}^{(1)}_{m}}\left(z,h\right)=\sqrt{\dfrac{2}{\pi}}\dfrac{1}{g_{ \mathit{e},m}(h)\mathrm{ce}_{m}\left(0,h^{2}\right)}\mathrm{Ce}_{m}\left(z,h^{ 2}\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.22.2" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E2">{\mathrm{Ms}^{(1)}_{m}}\left(z,h\right)=\sqrt{\dfrac{2}{\pi}}\frac{1}{g_{ \mathit{o},m}(h)\mathrm{se}_{m}'\left(0,h^{2}\right)}\mathrm{Se}_{m}\left(z,h^ {2}\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.22.3" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E3">{\mathrm{Mc}^{(2)}_{m}}\left(z,h\right)=\sqrt{\frac{2}{\pi}}\dfrac{1}{g_{ \mathit{e},m}(h)\mathrm{ce}_{m}\left(0,h^{2}\right)}\*\left(-f_{\mathit{e},m}( h)\mathrm{Ce}_{m}\left(z,h^{2}\right)+\dfrac{2}{\pi C_{m}(h^{2})}\mathrm{Fe}_{ m}\left(z,h^{2}\right)\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.22.4" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E4">{\mathrm{Ms}^{(2)}_{m}}\left(z,h\right)=\sqrt{\frac{2}{\pi}}\dfrac{1}{g_{ \mathit{o},m}(h)\mathrm{se}_{m}'\left(0,h^{2}\right)}\*\left(-f_{\mathit{o},m} (h)\mathrm{Se}_{m}\left(z,h^{2}\right)-\dfrac{2}{\pi S_{m}(h^{2})}\mathrm{Ge}_ {m}\left(z,h^{2}\right)\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C28.S22.SS1.p1.s2">
The joining factors in the above formulas are given by <Math equation-number="28.22.5" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E5">g_{\mathit{e},2m}(h)=(-1)^{m}\sqrt{\dfrac{2}{\pi}}\dfrac{\mathrm{ce}_{2m}\left (\frac{1}{2}\pi,h^{2}\right)}{A_{0}^{2m}(h^{2})},</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.22.6" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E6">g_{\mathit{e},2m+1}(h)=(-1)^{m+1}\sqrt{\frac{2}{\pi}}\dfrac{\mathrm{ce}_{2m+1} '\left(\frac{1}{2}\pi,h^{2}\right)}{hA_{1}^{2m+1}(h^{2})},</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.22.7" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E7">g_{\mathit{o},2m+1}(h)=(-1)^{m}\sqrt{\dfrac{2}{\pi}}\dfrac{\mathrm{se}_{2m+1} \left(\frac{1}{2}\pi,h^{2}\right)}{hB_{1}^{2m+1}(h^{2})},</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.22.8" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E8">g_{\mathit{o},2m+2}(h)=(-1)^{m+1}\sqrt{\dfrac{2}{\pi}}\dfrac{\mathrm{se}_{2m+2 }'\left(\frac{1}{2}\pi,h^{2}\right)}{h^{2}B_{2}^{2m+2}(h^{2})},</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.22.9" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E9">f_{\mathit{e},m}(h)=-\sqrt{\ifrac{\pi}{2}}g_{\mathit{e},m}(h){\mathrm{Mc}^{(2) }_{m}}\left(0,h\right),</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.22.10" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E10">f_{\mathit{o},m}(h)=-\sqrt{\ifrac{\pi}{2}}g_{\mathit{o},m}(h){\mathrm{Ms}^{(2) }_{m}}'\left(0,h\right),</Math> where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS1.p1.m1">A_{n}^{m}(h^{2})</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS1.p1.m2">B_{n}^{m}(h^{2})</Math> are as in ยง28.4(i), and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS1.p1.m3">C_{m}(h^{2})</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS1.p1.m4">S_{m}(h^{2})</Math> are as in ยง28.5(i).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C28.S22.SS1.p1.s3">
Furthermore, <Math equation-number="28.22.11" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E11">{\mathrm{Mc}^{(2)}_{m}}'\left(0,h\right)=\sqrt{\ifrac{2}{\pi}}g_{\mathit{e},m} (h),{\mathrm{Ms}^{(2)}_{m}}\left(0,h\right)=-\sqrt{\ifrac{2}{\pi}}g_{\mathit{o},m} (h),</Math> <Math equation-number="28.22.12" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E12">\mathrm{fe}_{m}'\left(0,h^{2}\right)=\tfrac{1}{2}\pi C_{m}(h^{2})\left(g_{ \mathit{e},m}(h)\right)^{2}\mathrm{ce}_{m}\left(0,h^{2}\right),\mathrm{ge}_{m}\left(0,h^{2}\right)=\tfrac{1}{2}\pi S_{m}(h^{2})\left(g_{ \mathit{o},m}(h)\right)^{2}\mathrm{se}_{m}'\left(0,h^{2}\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>

 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C28.S22.SS2">
<title>Noninteger <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.m1">\nu</Math></title>        
 
<para xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="28.22.13" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E13">{\mathrm{M}^{(1)}_{\nu}}\left(z,h\right)=\frac{{\mathrm{M}^{(1)}_{\nu}}\left(0 ,h\right)}{\mathrm{me}_{\nu}\left(0,h^{2}\right)}\mathrm{Me}_{\nu}\left(z,h^{2 }\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1.s2">
Here <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1.m1">\mathrm{me}_{\nu}\left(0,h^{2}\right)</Math> <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1.m2">(\neq 0)</Math> is given by (28.14.1) with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1.m3">z=0</Math> , and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1.m4">{\mathrm{M}^{(1)}_{\nu}}\left(0,h\right)</Math> is given by (28.24.1) with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1.m5">j=1</Math> , <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1.m6">z=0</Math> , and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1.m7">n</Math> chosen so that <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1.m8">|c_{2n}^{\nu}(h^{2})|=\max(|c_{2\ell}^{\nu}(h^{2})|)</Math> , where the maximum is taken over all integers <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1.m9">\ell</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="28.22.14" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S22.E14">{\mathrm{M}^{(2)}_{\nu}}\left(z,h\right)=\cot\left(\nu\pi\right){\mathrm{M}^{( 1)}_{\nu}}\left(z,h\right)-\frac{1}{\sin\left(\nu\pi\right)}{\mathrm{M}^{(1)}_ {-\nu}}\left(z,h\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C28.S22.SS2.p2.s1">
See also (28.20.13) and (28.20.14).
</sentence>

</para>
  
</subsection>
 
</section>
